                        div
                            span In the Application Admin page, select 
                            b=" Okta " 
                            span as the authentication method. This will display you customized 
                            b=" Login Redirect URI "
                            span which will be used to configure the App in the Okta dashboard.
                        img.capture(src="/help/okta/0.png" style="width: 40em;margin: auto;")

                        h3 Add a new OPkta Application
                        div 
                            span In your Okta Admin Portal, go to the 
                            b=" Applications "
                            span menu, and click 
                            b=" Add Application"                    
                        img.capture(src="/help/okta/1.png" style="width: 50em;margin: auto;")
                        div 
                            span In the new screen, click 
                            b=" Create New App"
                        img.capture(src="/help/okta/2.png" style="width: 50em;margin: auto;")
                        div 
                            span In the "Create a New Application Integration" form, select
                            b=" Web "
                            span in the dropdown list, and 
                            b=" OpenID Connect "
                            span as the Sign in method
                        img.capture(src="/help/okta/3.png" style="width: 30em;margin: auto;")
                        div
                            span Next, set the Application name, and fill the 
                            b=" Login redirect URIs "
                            span from the application configuration page, then click 
                            b=" Next"
                            span .
                        img.capture(src="/help/okta/4.png" style="width: 30em;margin: auto;")
                        div
                            span To finish, in the
                            b="Assignments "
                            span tab, assign the list of users or groups that ara allowed to use this app.
                        img.capture(src="/help/okta/5.png" style="width: 40em;margin: auto;")
                        h3 Finalize the auhentication configuration in the App Admin page
                        div
                            span Use the 
                            b=" ClientID, clientSecret "
                            span and
                            b=" Okta Domain "
                            span from the 
                            b=" General " 
                            span tab in the Okta Application to finish the configuration in the App Admin Page, and 
                            b=" Save "
                            span it.
                        img.capture(src="/help/okta/6.png" style="width: 40em;margin: auto;")
